## CONFIGURE SERVER
  ### [1] Install Fedora Server
  ### [2] Set static IP address on NIC:
      #### [a] Backup original /etc/sysconfig/network-scripts/ifcfg-<interface_name>
      #### You can create second interface to have internet access and PXE access interface
      #### [b] Modify /etc/sysconfig/network-scripts/ifcfg-<interface_name>
            Content:
            ```
             TYPE=Ethernet
             DEVICE=<interface_name>
             BOOTPROTO=none
             IPADDR=<static_IP>
             ONBOOT=yes 
             UUID=<leave_it>
            ```         
      #### [c] systemctl restart network
      
  ### [3] Set DHCP Server:
      #### [a] yum install dhcp
      #### [b] Backup /etc/dhcp/dhcpd.conf
      #### [c] Modify /etc/dhcp/dhcpd.conf
            Content:
            ```
            subnet <IP_range> netmask <netmask> {
              o
            
            
            }
            ```
      #### [d] systemctl restart dhcpd.service
  
  ### [4] Set TFTP Server:
      #### [a]
      #### [b]
 
## CONFIGURE HOST
  ### [1] Set NetBoot as first choice booting method
  ### [2] Done!
